Source...............: CD                                                            Hello, I Must Be Going! is the second studio album by English singer-songwriter Phil Collins. It was originally released 1 November 1982. This album's name comes from the Marx Brothers' song with the same name, featured in the movie Animal Crackers. The album was promoted with a tour of the same name. The album brought Collins his first nomination for British Male Artist at the Brit Awards in 1983.                 Track listing

All songs written and composed by Phil Collins, except "You Can't Hurry Love" by Holland-Dozier-Holland.
